valkyr — dual-licensed
========================

valkyr is available under either of:

  - the Apache License, Version 2.0 (see LICENSE-APACHE), OR
  - a commercial license offered by Foundation42 / Entrained.ai
    (see LICENSE-COMMERCIAL.md and contact chris@foundation42.org).

You may pick whichever fits your use case. Open-source users, students,
researchers, and most downstream projects should use Apache 2.0 — it
imposes no copyleft and grants explicit patent rights.

The commercial license is for organizations that want:

  - a path free of Apache 2.0's attribution / NOTICE-file requirements,
  - indemnification, support, or a contractual SLA,
  - use without distributing the corresponding NOTICE.

Both licenses cover the same code. There is no "open core" / "premium
features" split — the entire valkyr runtime, kernels, server, embed
surface, and tooling is available under either license at the licensee's
choice.

